##VIDEO MANAGER – merge – Combine Videos, Audio and Subtitles

This function enables flexible merging of:
- multiple videos (matched resolution and FPS through preprocessing)
- a video with external audio (e.g. microphone recording)
- a video with external subtitle (burned or soft)

# How it works
1. **Preprocessing**: All videos are transcoded to a uniform format/FPS. Optional pauses and a starting black screen can be inserted.
2. **Merging**: Uses the ffmpeg concat demuxer to combine all prepared files.

# Arguments (Flags)
#--------------------------------------------------------------
# General
- `--files`            		List of input files (optional, otherwise interactive selection)
- `--output FILE`      		Output filename [.mp4 will be added if missing]

# Merging multiple videos
- `--pause TIME`       		Pause (black screen + silent audio) between clips (sec / MM:SS / HH:MM:SS)
- `--offset TIME`      		Optional black screen at the very beginning (only for multi-video merge)
- `--target-res`       		Target resolution: `no-scale` (default), `smallest`, `average`, `largest`
   - `no-scale` keeps original sizes, padding with black bars as needed

# Merging video + audio/subtitle (2 files)
- `--offset TIME`      		Delay for audio or subtitle track (sec / MM:SS / HH:MM:SS)
- `--burn-subtitle`    		If set, the subtitle is burned into the video
- `--subtitle-name TXT`	Optional display name for soft subtitle (shown in VLC etc.)

# Special behavior
#----------------------------------------------------------------
- Already processed files (video or pause) are cached and reused
- Duplicate selections like `2,3,2` are supported and respected

# Output
#----------------------------------------------------------------
- Final video will match the chosen resolution and merge all clips seamlessly
- Temporary transcoded files are auto-deleted after processing

# Examples
#--------------------------------------------------
video merge --files clip1.mp4 mic.wav --offset 0:01
video merge --burn-subtitle --subtitle-name "German"
video merge --target-res no-scale --pause 1:30

#---
Note: `-movflags +faststart` is set by default for better compatibility with web players and soft subtitles.

